               <msContents>
                  <summary>Volume 2 of the <title>Ḥabīb al-Siyar</title> (Beloved of Biographies)
                     completed by the author <persName key="person_45109504"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard"
                        >Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ibn Humām al-Dīn (ca. 1475–1535)</persName> known as
                        <addName key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/"
                        >Khvāndamīr (1487–1524 CE)</addName>, in <date>937 AH (1530–31 CE)</date>.
                     A popular general history covering the pre-Islamic period up to the time of
                     Shāh Ismāʿīl I, the entire work consists of a preface, an introduction, three
                     volumes—each of which contains four sections appended with lists of names of
                     prominent figures associated with each period—followed by an epilogue. This
                     volume covers the early Islamic period up until the reign of the last
                     Khwarazmshāh <persName role="subject" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9442701">Jalāl
                        al-Dīn Mingburnu (r. 1220–1231)</persName>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_971-item1">
                     <author key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Khvānd Mīr, Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn
                           ibn Humām al-Dīn, ca. 1475-1535?</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">خواند مير، غياث الدين بن همام الدين</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Khvāndamīr</persName><lb/>
                        <persName type="alt" xml:lang="fa">خواندمير</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_645">Ḥabīb al-Siyar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_645">حبيب السير</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
